instruction:
It is known that the number of calls received by the paging station within the time interval $[ 0, t )$ $\{N(t), t \geq 0 \}$ follows a Poisson process, with an average of 2 calls received per minute. Given that 5 calls are received in the time interval $[ 0, 3 )$, find the probability of receiving 3 calls in the time interval $[ 0, 2 )$ is ().

Options:
A. $$
\frac{7 2} {2 4 9}
$$
B. $$
\frac{5 4} {2 3 3}
$$
C. $$
\frac{8 0} {2 4 3}
$$
D. $$
\frac{4 7} {2 5 3}
$$
E. $$
\frac{9 1} {2 4 1}
$$
F. $$
\frac{6 8} {2 4 5}
$$
G. $$
\frac{2 3} {2 4 7}
$$
H. $$
\frac{1 2} {2 5 3}
$$
I. $$
\frac{8 9} {2 2 3}
$$
J. $$
\frac{3 5} {4 4 3}
$$
